        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 2:56PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 255 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near White Oak to Tolarsville to Buie. Movement
was southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lumberton, Elizabethtown, Red Springs, St. Pauls, Bladenboro, Bladen
Community College, Ammon, Butters, Hestertown, Buie, Robeson
Community College, White Oak, Smiths, Howellsville, Duart,
Tolarsville, Tobermory, Ruskin, Barker Ten Mile, and Jerome.

This includes Interstate 95 in North Carolina between mile markers 13
and 32.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
